FBIS3-55552 "drsov006_b_94031" FBIS-SOV-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Independent Lawmakers Nominate Medvedev To Head Duma LD1001144094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1422 GMT 10 Jan 94 LD1001144094 Moscow ITAR-TASS Language: English Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] [Text] Moscow January 10 TASS -- Independent lawmakers in the Russian State Duma decided at their Monday conference to nominate Vladimir Medvedev, president of the Russian Union of Oil Manufacturers, for the post of chairman of the Federal Assembly's lower chamber. Medvedev told ITAR-TASS that if he is elected he will do a "specific practical work, as the task of deputies is to make laws". Independent deputies comprises 56 people now, and intend to register as a faction at the first session of the Duma.
